<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<suppressions xmlns="https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd">
    <!--
        False positive: dependency-check matches the MCP Kotlin SDK's version number (0.12.0)
        against cpe:/a:jetbrains:kotlin, i.e. it mistakes the Model Context Protocol SDK for the
        Kotlin language itself. The io.modelcontextprotocol artifacts are NOT the Kotlin language,
        so every jetbrains:kotlin CVE matched against them (old Kotlin CVEs and any future ones)
        is spurious. Suppress the jetbrains:kotlin CPE for all io.modelcontextprotocol packages.
        The actual Kotlin language version in use is governed by org.jetbrains.kotlin:* artifacts,
        which are scanned on their own and not suppressed here.
    -->
    <suppress>
        <notes><![CDATA[
            MCP Kotlin SDK (io.modelcontextprotocol) is mis-identified as cpe:/a:jetbrains:kotlin
            purely by version-number coincidence. It is not the Kotlin language runtime.
        ]]></notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/io\.modelcontextprotocol/.*$</packageUrl>
        <cpe>cpe:/a:jetbrains:kotlin</cpe>
    </suppress>

    <!--
        CVE-2026-53914: unsafe deserialization in Kotlin BUILD CACHE METADATA (CWE-502). The
        vulnerable component is Kotlin build tooling (compiler / Gradle plugin build cache), not
        the runtime libraries. dependency-check matches it against every jetbrains:kotlin artifact
        via broad CPE matching, including kotlin-stdlib and kotlin-reflect, which carry no
        build-cache logic and are not the vulnerable component.

        Corroboration: Sonatype OSS Index (coordinate-precise, not CPE-based) reports 0 known
        vulnerabilities for org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib:2.2.0, and the NVD record does not
        name stdlib/reflect as affected artifacts. This is an OWASP CPE false positive.

        The only version resolving the CVE is Kotlin 2.4.20, which is pre-release only
        (2.4.20-Beta1; no stable 2.4.20 exists on Maven Central). We do not ship a beta compiler,
        and these runtime artifacts are not the attack surface. Suppressed narrowly by CVE +
        artifact. Revisit and remove once a stable Kotlin >= 2.4.20 is available and adopted.
    -->
    <suppress>
        <notes><![CDATA[
            CVE-2026-53914 is a build-cache-metadata deserialization flaw in Kotlin build tooling,
            not in the kotlin-stdlib / kotlin-reflect runtime artifacts it is matched against
            (Sonatype OSS Index reports 0 vulns for kotlin-stdlib:2.2.0). Fix (2.4.20) is
            beta-only. Suppressed narrowly by CVE + artifact; revisit on stable 2.4.20.
        ]]></notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.jetbrains\.kotlin/kotlin-(stdlib|reflect)@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-53914</cve>
    </suppress>
</suppressions>
